title="Abstract Algebra">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Theorem 13.1.6</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-000F.xml"
addr="nt-000F"
title="Field extension">Field extension</fr:link>, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)\in \mathbb {F}[x]]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-001U.xml"
addr="ra-001U"
title="Irreducible element">irreducible</fr:link>, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \in \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> be a root of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}(\alpha )\subseteq \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-000M.xml"
addr="nt-000M"
title="Field Generated by elements">field generated</fr:link> by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex>. Then the map
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {split}e_{\alpha }\colon &\mathbb {F}[x]/(p(x))\to \mathbb {F}(\alpha )\\ &g(x)\mapsto  g(\alpha )\end {split}]]></fr:tex>
is an isomorphism.</fr:p>
 
   
