title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We see <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}[x]/(p(x))]]></fr:tex> is a field since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)]]></fr:tex> is irreducible. Since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{\alpha }]]></fr:tex> is nonzero, <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-000E.xml"
addr="nt-000E"
title="Morphisms of fields are injective or zero">it must be injective</fr:link>. Then the image of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{\alpha }]]></fr:tex> must be a subfield of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> and also contained in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}(\alpha )]]></fr:tex>, in particular the image of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{\alpha }]]></fr:tex> must contain <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F(\alpha )]]></fr:tex> is the minimal such field, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{\alpha }]]></fr:tex> must be surjective.</fr:p><html:span
